snippet: The Parliament will convene on Sunday to try to put together a government from Iraq’s often hostile factions, two weeks after a similar effort failed.
abstract: Iraq Parliament will reconvene again in effort to form new government from country's often hostile factions, two weeks after similar attempt failed.

byline.contributor: C.J. Chivers and an employee of The New York Times contributed reporting from Salahuddin Province, and Somini Sengupta from the United Nations.

lead_paragraph: The Parliament will convene on Sunday to try to put together a government from Iraq’s often hostile factions, two weeks after a similar effort failed.

headline.main: Iraqi Lawmakers to Reconvene in Effort to Form Government
headline.print_headline: Iraqi Lawmakers to Reconvene in Effort to Form Government
